# API Response Standards

## Context
- Defines standardized API response formats
- Ensures consistent HTTP status code usage
- Applies to all API endpoints

## Requirements
- All responses must use the standardized format via create_response()
- Include message, data (optional), errors (optional), and meta (optional) fields
- Use appropriate HTTP status codes: 200 (GET/PUT/PATCH), 201 (POST), 204 (DELETE), 4xx for client errors, 5xx for server errors
- Implement pagination for list endpoints returning multiple items
- Use Pydantic schemas for all request/response validation
- Include proper OpenAPI documentation
- Support API key authentication via X-API-Key header when enabled

## Response Format
```json
{
    "message": "Human-readable message",
    "data": {},     // Optional: Response payload
    "errors": [],   // Optional: List of error objects
    "meta": {}      // Optional: Metadata (pagination, etc.)
}
```

## Examples
<example>
# Good: Standardized response with proper status codes
from fastapi import status
from app.schema.api_response import create_response
from app.schema.user import UserListResponse, PaginationMeta

@router.get("/users")
async def list_users(
    page: int = Query(1, ge=1),
    per_page: int = Query(20, ge=1, le=100)
) -> JSONResponse:
    users, total = await user_service.list_users(page, per_page)
    
    return create_response(
        status_code=status.HTTP_200_OK,
        message="Users retrieved successfully",
        data=[user.model_dump() for user in users],
        meta={
            "pagination": {
                "page": page,
                "per_page": per_page,
                "total": total,
                "pages": (total + per_page - 1) // per_page
            }
        }
    )

@router.post("/users", status_code=status.HTTP_201_CREATED)
async def create_user(user_data: UserCreateRequest) -> JSONResponse:
    user = await user_service.create_user(user_data)
    return create_response(
        status_code=status.HTTP_201_CREATED,
        message="User created successfully",
        data=user.model_dump()
    )
</example>

